quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,HAPPY now the BELIEVERS
  23,2,Who humble them in their prayer
  23,3,And who keep aloof from vain words
  23,4,And who are doers of alms deeds
  23,5,And who restrain their appetites
  23,6,"Save with their wives, or the slaves whom their right hands possess: for in that case they shall be free from blame"
  23,7,But they whose desires reach further than this are transgressors
  23,8,And who tend well their trusts and their covenants
  23,9,And who keep them strictly to their prayers
  23,10,These shall be the heritors
  23,11,"Who shall inherit the paradise, to abide therein for ever"
  23,12,Now of fine clay have we created man
  23,13,"Then we placed him, a moist germ, in a safe abode"
  23,14,"Then made we the moist germ a clot of blood: then made the clotted blood into a piece of flesh; then made the piece of flesh into bones: and we clothed the bones with flesh: then brought forth man of yet another make - Blessed therefore be God, the most excellent of Makers"
  23,15,Then after this ye shall surely die
  23,16,Then shall ye be waked up on the day of resurrection
  23,17,"And we have created over you seven heavens: - and we are not careless of the creation"
  23,18,"And we send down water from the Heaven in its due degree, and we cause it to settle on the earth; - and we have power for its withdrawal"
  23,19,"And by it we cause gardens of palm trees, and vineyards to spring forth for you, in which ye have plenteous fruits, and whereof ye eat"
  23,20,And the tree that groweth up on Mount Sinai; which yieldeth oil and a juice for those who eat
  23,21,"And there is a lesson for you in the cattle: We give you to drink of what is in their bellies, and many advantages do ye derive from them, and for food they serve you"
  23,22,And on them and on ships are ye borne